&lt;p&gt;This is your chance to have a critical impact at a dynamic gaming company in the midst of an exciting globalization journey. You&#39;ll be joining the Group International Legal Department which oversees legal matters for the NetEase group and coordinates with the legal teams within each division of the group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a talented Group Transactional and Commercial Counsel.&amp;nbsp; In this leadership role, you will be advising on a dynamic range of M&amp;amp;A, investments and divestments across multiple jurisdictions, and technology, media and telecom and general commercial matters at the highest international standards, including licensing, outsourcing, software technology development and professional services agreements, innovative FinTech projects, regulatory matters and cross-border technology transfers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position will report to the General Counsel of NetEase, Inc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NetEase operates in multiple countries globally, and this role is primarily responsible for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Corporate Transactions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead deal execution on a wide range of corporate transactions, including structuring, drafting, and negotiating transaction documents for acquisitions, disposals, minority investments, fund investments, financing transactions and joint ventures across multiple jurisdictions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess and advise senior stakeholders on legal, regulatory, and commercial risks relating to corporate transactions.&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigate regulatory approvals including antitrust, foreign investment clearances, and securities law requirements across multiple jurisdictions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with legal team to provide end-to-end transaction support, including structuring, due diligence, drafting, negotiation, and completion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate closely with internal business teams (e.g., senior management of business units and the NetEase group, business development, finance, tax, etc.) on all aspects of transactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide legal support on post-transaction monitoring and corporate governance matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commercial Contract Management &amp;amp; TMT Advisory&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft, review, and negotiate a variety of TMT and other commercial agreements for the NetEase group and individual business units across multiple jurisdictions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pr

